( Win64, 1.1 stable )
If you change Y rotation to 180 or -180 inside `_input` and you use `move()` inside `_fixed_process` instead of having (0,180,0) rotation you'll get (-180,0,-180) rotation next frame. While it looks the same it can break a lot of logic inside a script.
Here's example code:

``` python
extends KinematicBody

func _ready():
    set_process_input(true)
    set_fixed_process(true)

func _input(ev):
    if ev.is_action("ui_up") and ev.is_pressed() and !ev.is_echo():
        set_rotation( Vector3(0,deg2rad(-180),0) )
    elif ev.is_action("ui_down") and ev.is_pressed() and !ev.is_echo():
        print(get_rotation()) # -180,0,-180

func _fixed_process(delta):
    move(Vector3(0,0,0))
```
